Paired-like factor classification

1 Goals

  1. Compare sequence conservation across all homeodomain transcription factors.

  2. Determine if there are residues specific to Paired-like homeodomains.

2 Define subclass families

2.1 Compile necessary data

  1. Read in all sequence information associated with homeobox from Uniprot (mySequence). 344 TFs

  2. Grab list of all homeodomains from CISBP and to ensure that we have all of the homeodomains from CISBP. CISBP also has a stronger curation than uniprot since it is based on DNA binding information instead of just sequence conservation. 229 TFs

  3. Import information on DNA binding domain location from Uniprot.


HDs not included in CISBP curation

Note: A manual entry has been added for the Drosophila Paired factor used in the Paired-dimer on DNA structure (1FJL). The S50Q mutation has been made to the entry!

3 Residue composition of classes

3.0.1 Define function to create sequence logos

The below function filters the DNA binding domain sequences by the given class/subclass/cooperativity status. It runs a multiple sequence alignment to match up sequences based on position. Due to transitions in formatting, I had to convert the msa to the bios2mds package to export the alignment. I then imported the alignment to pipe into the geom_logo plotting feature.

namespace <- matrix(data = c( "R",  "Basic",    "#255C99",
                              "H",  "Basic",    "#255C99",
                              "K",  "Basic",    "#255C99",

colnames(namespace) <- c("Residue", "Type", "Color")

col_scheme <- make_col_scheme(chars = namespace$Residue, 
                              groups = namespace$Type, 
                              cols = namespace$Color)


H <- data.frame(xmin = c(9.5, 27.5, 41.5), 
                xmax = c(22.5, 37.5, 56.5), 
                ymin = c(0,0,0), 
                ymax = c(4.5,4.5,4.5))

DifferentialAlign2seq <- function(data, column, filter1, filter2 = NA, norm = TRUE, tile = FALSE) {
  
  lower_range = 0 %>% as.character()
  outer_range = (60 + 2*flank) %>% as.character()
  
  tmp1 <- filter(data, !!rlang::sym(column) == filter1) %>%
    .$seqDBD %>%
    AAStringSet(.)
  
  names(tmp1) <- data %>%
    filter(!!rlang::sym(column) == filter1) %>%
    .$TF
  
  tmp1 %>%
    msa(type = "protein") %>%
    msaConvert(type = "bios2mds::align") %>%
    export.fasta(outfile = "take2.fa",
                 ncol = lengths(.) %>% max())
  
  SubsetClassAA1 <- readAAStringSet("take2.fa") %>%
    base::chartr(x = ., old = "-", new = "1")
  
  x1 <- as.character(tmp1, use.names = FALSE) %>%
    as.data.frame(., nm = "seq")
  
  x1_length <- length(SubsetClassAA1)
  
  
  plot1 <- ggplot() +
    geom_logo(x1$seq,
              stack_width = 0.75,
              namespace = namespace$Residue,
              col_scheme = col_scheme,
              seq_type = "other") +
    theme_logo() +
    theme(text = element_text(size = 32),
          legend.position = "none", 
          plot.title = element_text(size = 28)) +
    scale_x_continuous(labels = seq(from = 5, by = 5, to = 60 + flank), 
                       breaks = seq(from = 5, by = 5, to = 60 + 2*flank), 
                       expand = c(0,0), 
                       limits = c(0.5, 60.5)) + 
    ggtitle(paste(filter1, " (n = ", x1_length, ")", sep = "")) + 
    geom_rect(data = H, aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax), 
              color = "lightgray",
              alpha = 0.1) + 
    ylim(c(0,4.5))
  
  if (is.na(filter2)) {
    
    gridExtra::grid.arrange(plot1)
    
  }
  
  else {
    
    tmp2 <- data %>%
      filter(!!rlang::sym(column) == filter2) %>%
      .$seqDBD %>%
      AAStringSet(.)
    
    names(tmp2) <- data %>%
      filter(!!rlang::sym(column) == filter2) %>%
      .$TF
    
    tmp2 %>%
      msa(type = "protein") %>%
      msaConvert(type = "bios2mds::align") %>%
      export.fasta(outfile = "take2.fa",
                   ncol = lengths(.) %>% max())
    
    SubsetClassAA2 <- readAAStringSet("take2.fa") %>%
      base::chartr(x = ., old = "-", new = "1")
    
    x2 <- as.character(tmp2, use.names = FALSE) %>%
      as.data.frame(., nm = "seq")
    
    x2_length <- length(SubsetClassAA2)
    
    
    plot2 <- ggplot() +
      geom_logo(x2$seq,
                stack_width = 0.75,
                namespace = namespace$Residue,
                col_scheme = col_scheme,
                seq_type = "other") +
      theme_logo() +
      theme(text = element_text(size = 32),
            legend.position = "none") +
      scale_x_continuous(labels = seq(from = 2, by = 2, to = 60 + flank), 
                         breaks = seq(from = 2, by = 2, to = 60 + 2*flank), 
                         expand = c(0,0), 
                         limits = c(0.5, 60.5)) + 
      ggtitle(paste(filter2, " (n = ", x2_length, ")", sep = "")) + 
      geom_rect(data = H, aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax), 
                color = "lightgray",
                alpha = 0.1) + 
      ylim(c(0,4.5))
    
    
    g1 <- geom_logo(x1$seq, plot = FALSE) %>%
      group_by(position, letter) %>%
      mutate(group = "GROUP1")
    
    g2 <- geom_logo(x2$seq, plot = FALSE) %>%
      group_by(position, letter) %>%
      mutate(group ="GROUP2")
    
    g <- rbind(g1, g2) %>%
      group_by(position, letter, group) %>%
      summarise(y = mean(y)) %>%
      pivot_wider(names_from = "group", values_from = y)
    
    
    if (norm == TRUE) {
      max_GROUP1 <- max(g$GROUP1, na.rm = TRUE)
      max_GROUP2 <- max(g$GROUP2, na.rm = TRUE)
      
      diff <- max_GROUP2 - max_GROUP1
    } else {
      diff = 0
    }
    
    tot <- g %>%
      group_by(position) %>%
      summarize(count = n())
    
    l <- merge(tot, g, all.y = TRUE, by = "position") %>%
      mutate(GROUP2 = case_when(GROUP2 > 0 ~ GROUP2 - (diff / count),
                                GROUP2 ==0 ~ GROUP2)) %>%
      mutate(GROUP1 = ifelse(is.na(GROUP1), 0, GROUP1)) %>%
      mutate(GROUP2 = ifelse(is.na(GROUP2), 0, GROUP2)) %>%
      mutate(y = GROUP1 - GROUP2)  %>%
      dplyr::select(-c(GROUP1, GROUP2)) %>%
      ungroup() %>%
      pivot_wider(values_from = "y", names_from = "letter")
    
    
    l[is.na(l)] <- 0
    l <- l %>%
      as.matrix() %>%
      t()
    
    l <- l[-1, ]
    
    H <- data.frame(xmin = c(9.5, 27.5, 41.5), 
                    xmax = c(22.5, 37.5, 56.5), 
                    ymin = c(-4,-4,-4), 
                    ymax = c(4,4,4))
    
    plot3 <- ggplot() +
      geom_hline(yintercept = 0,
                 # linetype = "longdash",
                 color = "gray",
                 linewidth = 0.5) +
      annotate(geom = "rect", 
               xmin = c(25.5, 43.5), 
               xmax = c(26.5, 44.5), 
               ymin = c(-Inf, -Inf), 
               ymax = c(Inf, Inf), 
               fill = "lightblue", 
               alpha = 0.4) + 
      annotate(geom = "rect", 
               xmin = c(27.5), 
               xmax = c(28.5), 
               ymin = c(-Inf, -Inf), 
               ymax = c(Inf, Inf), 
               fill = "lightgray", 
               alpha = 0.4) + 
      geom_logo(l, method = "custom",
                stack_width = 0.75,
                namespace = namespace,
                col_scheme = col_scheme,
                seq_type = "other") +
      theme_logo() +
      theme(text = element_text(size = 32),
            legend.position = "none", 
            axis.ticks.length = unit(0, "pt"), 
            plot.title = element_text(size = 28)) +
      scale_x_continuous(labels = seq(from = 5, by = 5, to = 60 + flank), 
                         breaks = seq(from = 5, by = 5, to = 60 + 2*flank), 
                         expand = c(0,0), 
                         limits = c(0.5, 60.5)) + 
      scale_y_continuous(labels = c(-4, -2, 0, 2, 4), 
                         breaks = c(-4, -2, 0, 2, 4), 
                         limits = c(-4,4)) +
      ggtitle("Differential bit analysis") + 
      ylab(expression(paste(Delta, "Bit"))) +
      ylim(c(-4, 4))
    
    if ( tile == TRUE ) {   
      
      plot4 <- 
        data %>% 
        filter( (!!rlang::sym(column) == filter1)  | (!!rlang::sym(column) == filter2) ) %>%
        separate(seqDBD, into = ( c(0: (60 + 2*flank)) %>% as.character() ), sep = "") %>% 
        dplyr::select(-c("0")) %>%
        pivot_longer(( c(1: (60 + 2*flank)) %>% as.character() ),
                     names_to = "Position",
                     values_to = "Residue") %>%
        merge(., namespace) %>%
        mutate(Position = as.numeric(Position)) %>%
        ggplot(aes(x = Position,
                   y = reorder(TF, desc(!!rlang::sym(column))),
                   label = Residue,
                   color = Type)) +
        geom_text(size = 4) +
        theme_classic() +

4 Number of reasons ANTP cannot bind cooperatively to the P3 site

4.1 Version 1

conflictingResidues <- 
  dfDBD %>%
  select(-seq) %>% 
  filter(Class %in% c("ANTP", "Paired-like")) %>%
  mutate(R2 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 2, end = 2) %>%
           str_detect(., "R")) %>%
  mutate(R3 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 3, end = 3) %>%
           str_detect(., "R")) %>%
  mutate(pos_4 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 4, end = 4) %>%
           str_detect(., "E", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(P26 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 26, end = 26) %>%
           str_detect(., "P")) %>%
  mutate(pos_28 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 28, end = 28) %>%
           str_detect(., "R", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(E32 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 32, end = 32) %>%
           str_detect(., "E")) %>%
  mutate(E42 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 42, end = 42) %>%
           str_detect(., "E")) %>%
  mutate(pos_43 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 43, end = 43) %>%
           str_detect(., "R", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(R44 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 44, end = 44) %>%
           str_detect(., "Q", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(Q46 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 46, end = 46) %>%
           str_detect(., "R|K", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(pos50 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 50, end = 50) %>%
           str_detect("K", negate = TRUE)) %>%
  pivot_longer(c(R2:pos50), 
               names_to = "Residue", 
               values_to = "Present") %>%
  group_by(TF, Class) %>%
  summarize(Count = sum(!Present)) %>%
  arrange(Count)

conflictingResidues %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = Count, 
             x = reorder(TF, Count), 
             fill = Class)) + 
  geom_col(alpha = 0.5) + 
  ylab("Residue count") + 
  xlab("") + 
  ggtitle("Number of residues that conflict with P3 site cooperativity") + 
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), 
                     limits = c(0, 8.1), 
                     breaks = c(0:10)) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#A02B93", "#4EA72E"),

Changes

  • If DNA binding domain is identical between two proteins, they are represented by single column.

  • Columns are shaded to represent whether broken rule contributes or is critical to cooperativity.

dfDBDUnique <- dfDBD %>% filter(Class %in% c("ANTP", "Paired-like")) %>% distinct(., seqDBD, .keep_all = TRUE)

dfDBDConsolidated <- merge(dfDBDUnique, dfDBDMatching %>% select(TF, seqDBD), by = "seqDBD", all.x = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(label = case_when(is.na(TF.y) ~ TF.x, TRUE ~ paste(TF.x, "/", TF.y, sep = "")))



conflictingResidues <-

           str_detect(., "R", negate = TRUE)) %>%

           str_detect(., "E")) %>%
  mutate(E42 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 42, end = 42) %>%
           str_detect(., "E")) %>%

           str_detect(., "R", negate = TRUE)) %>%

  mutate(pos50 = str_sub(seqDBD, start = 50, end = 50) %>%

  group_by(label, Class, RuleType) %>%
  summarize(Count = sum(!Present))
